remarks: doi:10.11646/phytotaxa.403.2.6 The species is named D. medusae because of the shape and arrangement of its staminate inflorescences, short and dense, emerging all from the same axil (2–7 per node), resembling the snakes on Medusa’s head, the mythological Greek character.
